    <item><p><link xref="sessions#support"/></p></item>
  </list>
</section>

<section id="siko_bouterse">
  <title>Siko Bouterse</title>

  <media src="sikobouterse.jpg" width="160" height="160" style="floatend">
    <p>Siko Bouterse</p>
  </media>

  <p>Siko is an open collaboration junky and project-builder who
  works as a grantmaker at the Wikimedia Foundation. She runs
  Wikimedia’s Individual Engagement Grants Program and the
  Grants:IdeaLab, and she’s spent 2 years facilitating teams
  working on help documentation, volunteer onboarding, and social
  support systems for Wikipedia. In a former life, she was a
  localization and community manager; these days she’s mostly
  preoccupied by setting up experiments to engage volunteers in
  serious open-culture pursuits using playful structures.</p>

  <list style="compact">
    <item><p><link xref="sessions#teahouse"/></p></item>
    <item><p><link xref="sessions#support"/></p></item>
  </list>
</section>

<section id="jeremy_garcia">
  <title>Jeremy Garcia</title>

  <media src="jeremygarcia.jpg" width="160" height="160" style="floatend">
    <title>Jeremy Garcia</title>
  </media>

  <p>Jeremy is the Founder of
  <link href="http://linuxquestions.org/">LinuxQuestions.org</link>,
  and an ardent but realistic Open Source evangelist. Founded in
  2000, LQ is a friendly and active Linux community that served as
  the initial site in what has now become The Questions Network.
  Current member sites include
  <link href="http://androidquestions.org/">AndroidQuestions.org</link>,
  <link href="http://chromeosquestions.org/">ChromeOSQuestions.org</link> and
  <link href="http://linuxexchange.org/">LinuxExchange.org</link>.</p>

  <list style="compact">
    <item><p><link xref="sessions#support"/></p></item>
  </list>
</section>

